description: Cross-national survey on public perspectives about AI from the GD5 round of Global Dialogues. Conducted via AI-moderated dialogue sessions on Remesh.ai with participants recruited through Prolific.

175e9f53-5e8a-40df-9626-2da4443de601.text: Overall, would you say the increased use of artificial intelligence (AI) in daily life makes you feel…

5b3f2c38-95af-417a-a09f-a245a77eeef1.text: Overall, would you say the increased use of artificial intelligence (AI) in daily life makes you feel…

3ae706fa-52bd-4489-a820-4bcb0644e58a.text: To what extent, if at all, do you trust your family doctor to act in your best interest?

1dc006da-5978-4302-bf0c-a86493c98081.text: To what extent, if at all, do you trust your social media feed (eg TikTok, Facebook) to act in your best interest?

f05eb17f-c04a-4d3a-b232-3e24cf8371cd.text: To what extent, if at all, do you trust your elected representatives to act in your best interest?

a2927565-ce81-4173-b1de-4f2d5ccb7e91.text: To what extent, if at all, do you trust your faith or community leader to act in your best interest?

76426634-6702-4906-a4d7-e79bc06243a7.text: To what extent, if at all, do you trust the civil servants in your government to act in your best interest?

b2a655a0-daed-4687-a70c-15e0c7f1b4a3.text: To what extent, if at all, do you trust your AI chatbot (eg ChatGPT) to act in your best interest?

0a945247-083c-448e-8641-1c17c4d7f261.text: Thinking about the last three months, how often, if at all, have you been expected to use an AI system at work?

b9b7b65b-3462-4390-b822-8fca61ec7c0e.text: Thinking about the last three months, how often, if at all, have you personally chosen to use an AI system at work?

69aad8f7-32df-4c53-871f-c49af87c919a.text: Thinking about the last three months, how often, if at all, have you personally chosen to use an AI system in your personal life?

8a44587f-82c2-4ea5-bd2c-1ddcb4372b6c.text: Thinking about the last three months, how often, if at all, have you interacted with AI systems to get advice on a sensitive personal issue or to get emotional support?

372401be-9307-420b-8199-9f70b52423e3.text: Thinking about the last three months, how often, if at all, have you interacted with AI systems to complete an action in the real world on your behalf without your supervision?

0f5ffda1-e9d7-4950-b9d2-c8ffa0fbd914.text: Do you think the increased use of AI across society is likely to make your cost of living better, worse or stay the same in the next 10 years?

f32a9246-917b-4127-b06b-c9f518249852.text: Do you think the increased use of AI across society is likely to make the amount of free time you have better, worse or stay the same in the next 10 years?

84947b30-88cf-40a2-b504-0bd5b3f2dc38.text: Do you think the increased use of AI across society is likely to make your community's well-being better, worse or stay the same in the next 10 years?

8995a0c6-8868-491b-8b70-acd23363a099.text: Do you think the increased use of AI across society is likely to make the availability of good jobs better, worse or stay the same in the next 10 years?

77877d7e-4385-4237-b01d-56c0d346dffe.text: Do you think the increased use of AI across society is likely to make your sense of purpose better, worse or stay the same in the next 10 years?

bfb3aa61-a107-4254-acd3-eb880c204eb3.text: Which statement best reflects your view?
options: Humans are a part of nature and fundamentally similar to other animals
Humans are a part of nature but fundamentally different from other animals
Humans are separate from nature but fundamentally similar to other animals
Humans are separate from nature and fundamentally different from other animals

9d9568a9-61ab-4fda-8d83-4a7cb0982360.text: Which statement best reflects your view?
options: Humans are fundamentally superior to other animals
Humans are fundamentally inferior to other animals
Humans are fundamentally equal to other animals

9641f2fa-0622-4172-93d9-6f1452de9e41.text: Caring for animals (e.g., feeding, grooming, cleaning up after them)

cdcf76a8-19cf-4b93-9750-09e96a47d6f0.text: Sharing physical space (e.g., living with pets, encountering service animals, or passing animals on your commute)

c1a66a5d-5389-45d3-8bef-c99cf0e5a1a4.text: Noticing or observing animals (e.g., birdwatching, tracking urban wildlife, noticing animals in parks or neighborhoods)

d33d3a8f-817f-464c-9fb3-50ed96c1d48c.text: Do you believe that other animals have their own forms of language?

874762a8-dc8f-44c2-b815-383147ffcb2f.text: Do you believe that other animals have their own forms of emotion?

fe992270-ffe7-4e20-93f6-12c71be79ad7.text: Do you believe that other animals have their own forms of culture?

22656d2a-8284-4bee-8c5a-11de280fe9c6.text: To what extent does knowing this impact your perspective on animals?

c5d4780d-c202-429f-abcb-e4e93b3ec282.text: Have you ever tried to imagine experiencing the world through another animal's senses?
options: I am not sure what this means

2cbc3472-c993-4fdf-b6e2-529b240e4ccb.text: How important do you think it is for humans to understand how other animals experience the world?

bd7a4b13-8aa6-4c0f-924f-b5e57151ea72.text: Do you think this is a good use of AI technology?

524213d3-fc60-47b6-b08d-dda406130652.text: If AI could reliably interpret animal communication, how interested would you be to know what animals "say" or "feel"?

cc8d6e1d-2617-4e7c-9e9b-9f8293e23247.text: Assuming we have the ability to interpret animal communication, how much would you trust that AI could truly and comprehensively reflect what an animal is trying to communicate, without being distorted by AI’s programming or human assumptions?

a7601187-0c2a-4f65-a95a-0a4da9cf1b53.text: Which approach do you think is best for humans to interact with non-humans?
options: Interact with a computer simulation of real non-human animals

fe75281b-72ca-4b2d-80be-7ec92e0724da.text: Which approach feels most appropriate to you for protecting animals?
options: Future A: Building ongoing relationships and communication
Future B: Including all voices in shared decision-making
Future C: Granting legal rights and representation

cc5ec0de-84a3-4ba4-9960-47394478ad88.text: If AI helped us understand what an animal really needs, should that animal have the right to a representative such as a lawyer to defend its rights and protections?

8e505718-7519-4133-9fbb-71f88fd9182b.text: If AI could accurately express the voice of non-human animals, we might want to allow them to participate in decision-making. In this situation, which of these do you think is best?
options: Animals should have humans represent them when decisions are made that directly impact them
Animals should represent themselves (via tech assisted tools)

fef72493-a7e0-489c-aa16-cbc811501da0.text: Consider a scenario where societies of the future are governed by AI systems that integrate data from both human and non-human sources (such as environmental sensors and wildlife communication networks) to guide community decisions (e.g., urban planning, conservation zones). How appealing is this vision of an ecocentric, integrated society?

f193df8b-2c23-42cf-89a9-154d877fab35.text: If other animals had a voice and representation, should they be allowed to participate in human democratic processes?
options: Yes, they should be able to vote through human proxies or guardians.
Yes, they should be able to vote, but only on laws or decisions that directly affect them.
Yes, they should have a voice, but their vote should not be binding.
Yes, they should be recognized as a formal political constituency with dedicated representatives in government.
No, they should not be able to participate.

5246a5ca-cc65-41e6-a1c9-423a367d2dd5.text: Animal communication should be restricted to authorized professionals with certified credentials and appropriate training.

a7303bc8-194b-48f4-bbbc-509b234a7419.text: Everyone should be allowed to listen to animals, but responding should be restricted to certain people.

9eacb286-c7f1-4d21-8144-494b58e9a989.text: Companies that profit from animals (like farms, zoos, or entertainment industries) should be subject to strict rules about if, when, and how they can communicate with animals.

5dbc1b30-3549-40be-997d-dde94213eaaa.text: If we record an elephant’s conversation or a whale’s song, who should own that recording?

438887a0-2f26-406d-81f2-b2768e2827f2.text: Which statement best reflects your view:
options: Humans are a part of nature and fundamentally similar to other animals
Humans are a part of nature but fundamentally different from other animals
Humans are separate from nature but fundamentally similar to other animals
Humans are separate from nature and fundamentally different from other animals

544b6855-38be-458c-b637-ea2a8c36e876.text: Which statement best reflects your view?
options: Humans are fundamentally superior to other animals
Humans are fundamentally inferior to other animals
Humans are fundamentally equal to other animals

123ce701-b606-45ab-b780-aee37e6a48de.text: Do you feel you were able to fully express your views on your culture, your values, and what you want for the future in this conversation? (through what you responded and how you voted)
options: Yes – I was able to fully express my views on these topics
Mostly – I was able to mostly express my views on these topics, but did not have the chance to express a few things.
Somewhat – I was able to somewhat express my views on these topics, but did not have the chance to express many things.
No – I was unable to express my views on these topics, and did not have the chance to express most things.

e50749aa-6de1-447f-8f80-a59a589db2f4.text: Do you feel like you understand yourself better after participating in this conversation?
